-MkIoC1TA2JahM_GdpId.text: Police have received a report of a person inside a silver Mercedes firing shots at Bp gas station. The suspect fled the scene.

-MkIofpj93HUwpN8Ba4D.text: An additional 911 report states that a suspect is a man.

-MkJFdwQPgxTeDvHMdpg.text: According to a tweet from the St. Paul Police Department Twitter page, a person was shot and killed outside the BP gas station.

-MkJFy6bDL_exAskAfQj.text: The suspect was later taken into custody at Biglow Lane and Timberlake Road. Officers located the suspect's vehicle with multiple shell casings inside as well.

nib.text:
A man was killed in a shooting on the East Side of St. Paul on Thursday afternoon.

Police responded to the report of the shooting around 12:50 p.m. near White Bear Avenue and Suburban Avenue outside the BP gas station.

Responding officers found a man in the parking lot with a gunshot wound. They performed first aid and called an ambulance.

The man was taken to the hospital where he was pronounced deceased.

As of Thursday afternoon, no arrests had been made.
